<a id="a6a00d8341c4eab53ef0148c6dbb05b970c"></a>


<h3>IRS Agent Charged With Stealing $160k of Tax Refunds</h3>


<a style="float: right;" onclick="window.open( this.href, '_blank', 'width=640,height=480,scrollbars=no,resizable=no,toolbar=no,directories=no,location=no,menubar=no,status=no,left=0,top=0' ); return false" href="http://taxprof.typepad.com/.a/6a00d8341c4eab53ef0148c6dbafc4970c-popup"><img class="asset  asset-image at-xid-6a00d8341c4eab53ef0148c6dbafc4970c" style="width: 135px; margin: 0px 0px 5px 5px;" title="IRS Logo" src="http://taxprof.typepad.com/.a/6a00d8341c4eab53ef0148c6dbafc4970c-150wi" alt="IRS Logo" /></a> NBC New York, <a href="http://www.nbcnewyork.com/news/local-beat/IRS-Agent-Accused-of-Stealing-Tax-Refunds-112101854.html" target="_blank">IRS Agent Accused of Stealing Tax Refunds</a>:
<blockquote>
<p>Fern Stephens, a revenue officer at the IRS, is being charged by the U.S. Attorney's office for stealing more than $160,000 in unclaimed tax funds from 12 taxpayers, according to federal court documents. If convicted of all counts of mail fraud, theft of gonvernment funds, and unlawful access of a government computer, Stephens faces a maximum sentence of 35 years in prison.</p>
</blockquote>



