<a id="a6a00d8341c4eab53ef0147e0c69dac970b"></a>


<h3>Court: FedEx Drivers Are Independent Contractors, Not Employees</h3>


<a style="float: right;" onclick="window.open( this.href, '_blank', 'width=640,height=480,scrollbars=no,resizable=no,toolbar=no,directories=no,location=no,menubar=no,status=no,left=0,top=0' ); return false" href="http://taxprof.typepad.com/.a/6a00d8341c4eab53ef0148c6d0916a970c-popup"><img class="asset  asset-image at-xid-6a00d8341c4eab53ef0148c6d0916a970c" style="width: 175px; margin: 0px 0px 5px 5px;" title="FedEx" src="http://taxprof.typepad.com/.a/6a00d8341c4eab53ef0148c6d0916a970c-150wi" alt="FedEx" /></a> The U.S. District Court for the Northern District of Indiana has held in a consolidated, multi-district class action that&nbsp;most FedEx&nbsp;drivers are independent contractors rather than employees. <span class="asset  asset-generic at-xid-6a00d8341c4eab53ef0148c6d08b0e970c"><a href="http://taxprof.typepad.com/files/in-re-fedex-ground-package.pdf">In re FedEx Ground Package System, Inc.</a></span>, No. 3:05-cv-00390 (Dec. 13, 2010).
<ul>
<li><a href="http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-12-15/fedex-wins-ruling-that-contract-drivers-seeking-benefits-aren-t-employees.html" target="_blank">Bloomberg</a></li>
<li><a href="http://www.nytimes.com/2010/12/15/business/15fedex.html?src=busln" target="_blank">New York Times</a></li>
<li><a href="http://online.wsj.com/article/SB10001424052748704694004576020353665917530.html?mod=googlenews_wsj" target="_blank">Wall Street Journal</a></li>
</ul>



