<a id="a6a00d8341c4eab53ef0148c6d0a946970c"></a>


<h3>Bell: Z-scores in the 2011 U.S. News Rankings</h3>


<a href="http://www.chapman.edu/law/faculty/bell.asp" target="_blank"></a><a style="float: right;" onclick="window.open( this.href, '_blank', 'width=640,height=480,scrollbars=no,resizable=no,toolbar=no,directories=no,location=no,menubar=no,status=no,left=0,top=0' ); return false" href="http://taxprof.typepad.com/.a/6a00d8341c4eab53ef0148c6d0a7d7970c-popup"><img class="asset  asset-image at-xid-6a00d8341c4eab53ef0148c6d0a7d7970c" style="width: 175px; margin: 0px 0px 5px 5px;" title="U.S. News Logo" src="http://taxprof.typepad.com/.a/6a00d8341c4eab53ef0148c6d0a7d7970c-200wi" alt="U.S. News Logo" /></a><a href="http://www.chapman.edu/law/faculty/bell.asp" target="_blank"> Tom Bell</a> (Chapman) has published his wonderful annual listing of the&nbsp;<a href="http://agoraphilia.blogspot.com/2010/12/z-scores-in-model-of-2011-usn-law.html" target="_blank">z-scores</a> of each school in the Top 50 of&nbsp;the U.S. News law school rankings.&nbsp;The z-scores measure how well each school performed relative to its peers.&nbsp; Tom's rankings are especially important in those categories in which U.S. News does not publicly disclose its data (expenditures per student, financial aid per student).



<!-- AddThis Button BEGIN -->
<div><script type="text/javascript">var addthis_pub="paulcaron";</script><a href="http://www.addthis.com/bookmark.php" onmouseover="return addthis_open(this, '', encodeURIComponent('http://taxprof.typepad.com/taxprof_blog/2010/12/bell-.html'), encodeURIComponent('Bell: Z-scores in the 2011 U.S. News Rankings'));" onmouseout="addthis_close()" onclick="return addthis_sendto()" title="Bookmark and Share" target="_blank"><img src="http://s7.addthis.com/static/btn/lg-share-en.gif" width="125" height="16" alt="Bookmark and Share" style="border:0"/></a><script type="text/javascript" src="http://s7.addthis.com/js/200/addthis_widget.js"></script></div>
