<a id="a6a00d8341c4eab53ef0148c6cbd983970c"></a>


<h3>Christmas Gifts for that Special Tax Person</h3>


<a href="http://www.forcounsel.com/default_c.asp"></a><a style="float: right;" onclick="window.open( this.href, '_blank', 'width=640,height=480,scrollbars=no,resizable=no,toolbar=no,directories=no,location=no,menubar=no,status=no,left=0,top=0' ); return false" href="http://taxprof.typepad.com/.a/6a00d8341c4eab53ef0148c6cbdbf9970c-popup"><img class="asset  asset-image at-xid-6a00d8341c4eab53ef0148c6cbdbf9970c" style="width: 150px; margin: 0px 0px 5px 5px;" title="1913 Tax Form" src="http://taxprof.typepad.com/.a/6a00d8341c4eab53ef0148c6cbdbf9970c-150wi" alt="1913 Tax Form" /></a><a href="http://www.forcounsel.com/default_c.asp"> For Counsel (Products and Gifts for Lawyers)</a> sells an exact <a href="http://www.forcounsel.com/productDetails_c.asp?productid=1398F">reproduction of the original 1913 Form 1040</a>:
<blockquote dir="ltr">
<p style="margin-right: 0px;" dir="ltr">Four pages long, including one page of instructions. Impressively framed in classic mahogany with beaded edge and segmented mat of ivory. Brass plate mounted on the mat states: "1913 Inaugural Form 1040." Framed dimensions are 30" by 24". Comes with Plexiglas and all accessories for hanging.</p>
</blockquote>
<p style="margin-right: 0px;" dir="ltr">Unframed copies of&nbsp;the 1913 Form 1040 can be downloaded for free at the <a href="http://www.irs.gov/pub/irs-utl/1913.pdf" target="_blank">IRS</a>&nbsp;and the <a href="http://taxhistory.org/thp/1040forms.nsf/WebByYear/1913/$file/1040_1913.pdf" target="_blank">Tax History Project</a>.</p><p></p>



