<a id="a6a00d8341c4eab53ef0147e0a91d10970b"></a>


<h3>Pepperdine Dean Finalists</h3>


<a style="float: right;" onclick="window.open( this.href, '_blank', 'width=640,height=480,scrollbars=no,resizable=no,toolbar=no,directories=no,location=no,menubar=no,status=no,left=0,top=0' ); return false" href="http://taxprof.typepad.com/.a/6a00d8341c4eab53ef0147e0a8f095970b-popup"><img class="asset  asset-image at-xid-6a00d8341c4eab53ef0147e0a8f095970b" style="width: 175px; margin: 0px 0px 5px 5px;" title="Pepperdine" src="http://taxprof.typepad.com/.a/6a00d8341c4eab53ef0147e0a8f095970b-200wi" alt="Pepperdine" /></a> Pepperdine has <a href="http://pepperdinelawdeans.posterous.com/dean-search-update-3" target="_blank">announced</a> that the faculty will be voting on Friday to send to the university administration its recommendations for a new Dean to replace&nbsp;the departed&nbsp;Ken Starr (who <a href="http://taxprof.typepad.com/taxprof_blog/2010/02/pepperdine-dean.html" target="_blank">resigned in June</a> to assume the Presidency of Baylor University). The five dean finalists are:
<ul>
<li><a href="http://law.pepperdine.edu/academics/faculty/default.php?faculty=richard_cupp" target="_blank">Richard L.&nbsp;Cupp</a> (John W. Wade Professor of Law, Pepperdine)</li>
<li><a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Robert_P._George" target="_blank">Robert P. George</a> (McCormick Professor of Jurisprudence and&nbsp;Director, James Madison Program in American Ideals and Institutions, Princeton)</li>
<li><a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Russell_K._Osgood" target="_blank">Russell K. Osgood</a> (former President, Grinnell; former Dean (and Tax Prof), Cornell)&nbsp;</li>
<li><a href="http://law.pepperdine.edu/academics/faculty/default.php?faculty=timothy_perrin&amp;FullBio=1" target="_blank">L. Timothy Perrin</a> (Vice Dean and Professor of Law, Pepperdine)</li>
<li><a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Deanell_Tacha" target="_blank">Deanell Reece Tacha</a> (Judge, U.S. Court of Appeals,&nbsp;10th Circuit; former Vice Chancellor of Academic Affairs and Professor of Law,&nbsp; Kansas)</li>
</ul>



